#Approach:

Approach:

Is question me linked list me sirf 0, 1, 2 diye hue hain.
Hume in-place sort karna hai (nodes change karne hain, values nahi).

Hum 3 dummy linked list banaenge:
Zero list
One list
Two list

Step 1:
Traverse original linked list.

Step 2:
Agar node.data == 0 → zero list me daal do
Agar node.data == 1 → one list me daal do
Agar node.data == 2 → two list me daal do

Step 3:
Ab tino lists ko connect karo:
Zero → One → Two

Step 4:
Return zeroHead.next

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1) (only pointers used)

Ye Dutch National Flag problem ka linked list version hai.

#Code:

/*
Definition of singly linked list:
class ListNode{
    public int data;
    public ListNode next;
    ListNode() { data = 0; next = null; }
    ListNode(int x) { data = x; next = null; }
    ListNode(int x, ListNode next) { data = x; this.next = next; }
}
*/

class Solution {
    public ListNode sortList(ListNode head) {

        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }

        ListNode zeroHead = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode oneHead = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode twoHead = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode zero = zeroHead;
        ListNode one = oneHead;
        ListNode two = twoHead;

        ListNode temp = head;

        while(temp != null){
            if(temp.data == 0){
                zero.next = temp;
                zero = zero.next;
            }
            else if(temp.data == 1){
                one.next = temp;
                one = one.next;
            }
            else{
                two.next = temp;
                two = two.next;
            }
            temp = temp.next;
        }
        zero.next = oneHead.next;
        one.next = twoHead.next;
        two.next = null;

        return zeroHead.next;

    }
}
